article.headline: Coppin St 75, Bethune Cookman 65
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Guards Tywain McKee and Darryl Roberts combined for 39 points to carry Coppin State to a 75-65 triumph over Bethune-Cookman College Saturday. McKee scored 20 points and Roberts 19 as the visiting Eagles won for the first time this season after 12 losses. CSU is now 1-1 in MEAC play. Bethune-Cookman (4-9, 1-2), which dropped its third straight, was headed by Antonio Webb's 23 points and Michael Williams' 18. Coppin State, winner of the last eight meetings with Bethune-Cookman, trailed by seven points, 49-42, with 12:03 to play. McKee and Roberts led a 22-7 run that pushed the Eagles to a ten-point edge, 66-56, with 3:33 to play. During that last 11 minutes, the Eagles did what Bethune-Cookman couldn't do the rest of the game--hit free throws. Coppin State closed out the game by hitting 14 of 16 foul shots, six by Roberts, who for the game hit 13 of 14. They hit 28-for-32 (87.5 percent) for the game. The Wildcats managed only two of 11 free throws over that final 12:03. Coppin State is now 39-6 all-time against Bethune-Cookman and owns a 19-3 mark in games played in Daytona Beach.
